definition:
The "Shoggoth Meme" in the context of artificial intelligence is a viral illustration and metaphor used by AI researchers and enthusiasts to represent a large language model's (LLM) inscrutable, potentially alien, and powerful nature, which is hidden behind a seemingly friendly and harmless user interface. 
The meme originated in a December 2022 tweet by user @TetraspaceWest and was later popularized by The New York Times tech columnist Kevin Roose as "the most important meme in A.I.". 
 @eng

